Create
mkdir testproject
cd testproject
git init

Modify
git add foo.txt (or git add .)
git commit
git mv
git rm

Inspect
git log
git status
git diff
git show (last Commit)

Possible Workflow
(this is just an example!)

some editing
git diff status - to see what files you changed
git diff [files] - to see the changes
git commit -a [-m <message>]

Remote repositories
c
Copy repository
git clone <repository>
 * repository = URL (file, http, ssh, ...)
 * creates a complete local copy of the repository
 * links it to the remore repository (origin)(you cal also link to <repository> later)
 
 RECEIVE CHANGES
 git pull - Send Changes [git fetch git merge to inspect changes]
 git push
